sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: argB
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: argB cassette, selection marker for Aspergillus nidulans
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The Aspergillus nidulans gene argB encodes ornithine transcarbamylase and can be used as an auxotrophic marker in the filamentous fungi A. nidulans and A. niger. The successfull use of argB as a selection marker has been documented and described extensively in the literature.
